item.title: Need Help Import
item.dc:creator: @sk8rdude461 sk8rdude461
item.description:
@sk8rdude461 wrote:

How to set up an import (For Non-IDE users(because IDE’s do it for you):

  1. Look at the top of the class file you are going to import for it’s package:
    package server.model.players.Content;
  2. remove the word “package” and replace it with “import” (NOTE: Not in the actual file, I suggest you copy the line and modify it in another text editor.)
  3. Remove the semicolon, add the name of said file you are importing (in this case, PriceChecker), then re-add the semicolon at the end:
    server.model.players.Content.PriceChecker;
  4. Add to the list of imports in the file you want.

If you are still getting errors. Either the package is set up wrong. Meaning you copied the price checker and put it in the wrong folder, or you managed to do something wrong.
